[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis is a **Remote Code Execution [0m[1;39m([0m[39mRCE[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m** vulnerability caused by unsafe Java [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeserialization. The security issue is classified as high severity, as it allows [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munrestricted class/object creation based on externally controlled data, which can [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlead to arbitrary code execution depending on the classes available on the [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mapplication's classpath.[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Issue Details[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe vulnerability manifests during the parsing of RTF documents when the parser [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mencounters embedded objects. The stack trace reveals the following execution flow:[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. The RTF parser [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`RTFParser`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m processes an RTF file through its `[0m[1;35mparse[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mparseInline[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` methods[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. The `TextExtractor` component extracts content and processes group endings via [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mextract[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;35mprocessGroupEnd[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` methods[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. The `[0m[1;35mRTFEmbObjHandler.handleCompletedObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method is invoked to handle [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39membedded objects [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m217[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. This handler calls `[0m[1;35mObjectInputStream.readObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to deserialize the embedded [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mobject[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. During deserialization, a custom `[0m[1;35mreadObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method is invoked [0m[1;39m([0m[39mat [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mjaz.Zer.readObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` line [0m[1;36m377[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. The security issue is detected and reported by Jazzer's security hooks at [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mjaz.Zer.reportFinding[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m110[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Key Observations[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Deserialization Point**: The vulnerability occurs at [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mRTFEmbObjHandler.handleCompletedObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m217[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, where Java's native [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mObjectInputStream.readObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` is called without apparent safeguards against [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmalicious payloads.[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Attack Vector**: RTF files can contain embedded OLE objects that are [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mserialized Java objects. An attacker can craft a malicious RTF file with a [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mspecially crafted serialized object that, when deserialized, executes arbitrary [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcode.[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Detection Mechanism**: The Jazzer fuzzer successfully identified this [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvulnerability through its security hooks that monitor dangerous operations like [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munrestricted deserialization.[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Deduplication Token**: The issue has been assigned token `aa5f725795b842b8` [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfor tracking and deduplication purposes.[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Areas Requiring Investigation[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTo gain a holistic understanding of this security issue, the following components [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mshould be investigated:[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **RTFEmbObjHandler Class**: Particularly the `[0m[1;35mhandleCompletedObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m217[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to understand how embedded objects are processed and [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeserialized. This is the primary location where the vulnerability manifests.[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **RTF Parsing Pipeline**: The complete flow from `RTFParser` → `TextExtractor` →[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`RTFEmbObjHandler` to understand how embedded object data is extracted from RTF [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfiles and passed to the deserialization routine.[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Object Stream Processing**: How the parser identifies and extracts serialized [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mJava objects from RTF embedded objects [0m[1;39m([0m[39mOLE objects[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and prepares them for [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeserialization.[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Current Security Controls**: Whether any validation, filtering, or [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallowlist/blocklist mechanisms exist for deserialization within the RTF parser or [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe broader Tika framework.[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Supported Embedded Object Types**: What types of embedded objects the RTF [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparser supports and which of these involve Java deserialization.[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. **Dependencies and Classpath**: What libraries and classes are available on the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtypical deployment classpath that could be exploited through deserialization gadget[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchains.[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. **Usage Context**: How the RTF parser is typically deployed and whether [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39muser-supplied RTF files are processed, which would make this vulnerability [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexploitable by external attackers.[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Analysis[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Root Cause[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe vulnerability is in `[0m[1;35mRTFEmbObjHandler.handleCompletedObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` at lines [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m213[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m224[0m[39m, where Java objects embedded in RTF files via the `\javaobjdata` control [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mword are deserialized without any validation using [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mObjectInputStream.readObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`. This allows arbitrary code execution if malicious[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mserialized objects with gadget chain classes are present on the classpath.[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Key Observations[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Vulnerable Code Path**: The deserialization occurs when `state == [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mEMB_STATE.JAVA_OBJDATA` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m213[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m224[0m[39m in RTFEmbObjHandler.java[0m[1;39m)[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Limited Usage**: The deserialized object is only used to extract:[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Class name via `[0m[1;35mobj.getClass[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m218[0m[1;39m)[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - String representation via `[0m[1;35mobj.toString[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m221[0m[1;39m)[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   This suggests the actual object instantiation is unnecessary for the feature's [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpurpose.[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Safe Alternative Pattern**: The `EMB_STATE.OBJDATA` path [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m191[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m198[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdemonstrates safe embedded object handling using `RTFObjDataParser` which extracts [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbinary data without deserialization.[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Existing Configuration Pattern**: The codebase has established patterns for [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msecurity-related configuration flags:[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `@Field` annotation for configurable options[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `ignoreListMarkup` boolean flag [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m57[0m[39m in RTFParser.java[0m[1;39m)[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Configuration passed through constructor chain: RTFParser → RTFEmbObjHandler[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **No Breaking Harness Code**: The fix will not modify harness/fuzzing code - [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39monly the vulnerable production code in the RTF parser.[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Critical Logic to Preserve[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The OBJDATA and PICT handling paths must remain unchanged [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m191[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m211[0m[39m in [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mRTFEmbObjHandler.java[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Exception handling in `[0m[1;35mprocessGroupEnd[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m1476[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1477[0m[39m in TextExtractor.java[0m[1;39m)[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmust catch the new security exception[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Metadata extraction flow for non-Java embedded objects must continue working[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Test file processing for safe embedded objects must not be affected[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Approach: Disable Java Deserialization by Default with Opt-In Flag[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mI will implement a configuration-based approach that **disables Java object [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeserialization by default** while allowing explicit opt-in if absolutely [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnecessary. This follows the [0m[32m"secure by default"[0m[39m principle and existing Tika [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconfiguration patterns.[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Implementation Steps[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m#### Step [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m: Add Configuration Flag to RTFParser[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mIn `RTFParser.java` [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m57[0m[39m, after `ignoreListMarkup`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Add a new `@Field` annotated boolean: `private boolean allowJavaSerializedObjects[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m= false;`[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Default value is `false` for security [0m[1;39m([0m[39msecure by default[0m[1;39m)[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Add getter/setter methods following the pattern of `ignoreListMarkup`[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m#### Step [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m: Update RTFEmbObjHandler Constructor[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mIn `RTFEmbObjHandler.java` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m84[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m90[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Modify constructor signature to accept the new boolean flag:[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```java[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  protected [0m[1;35mRTFEmbObjHandler[0m[1;39m([0m[39mContentHandler handler, Metadata metadata, [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                             ParseContext context, int memoryLimitInKb,[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                             boolean allowJavaSerializedObjects[0m[1;39m)[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Store the flag as a private instance field[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m#### Step [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m: Update RTFParser to Pass Configuration[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mIn `RTFParser.java` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m92[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m93[0m[39m in `[0m[1;35mparseInline[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Pass the new flag when creating RTFEmbObjHandler:[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```java[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  RTFEmbObjHandler embObjHandler = new [0m[1;35mRTFEmbObjHandler[0m[1;39m([0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      handler, metadata, context, [0m[1;35mgetMemoryLimitInKb[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallowJavaSerializedObjects[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m#### Step [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m: Add Security Check in handleCompletedObject[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mIn `RTFEmbObjHandler.java` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m213[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m224[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Add check before deserialization:[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```java[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mstate == EMB_STATE.JAVA_OBJDATA[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m!allowJavaSerializedObjects[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          throw new [0m[1;35mTikaException[0m[1;39m([0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              [0m[32m"Java object deserialization is disabled for security reasons. "[0m[39m +[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              [0m[32m"Set [0m[32mallowJavaSerializedObjects[0m[32m=[0m[32mtrue[0m[32m in RTFParser configuration to [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32menable this feature."[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Existing deserialization code [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m214[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m224[0m[1;39m)[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m#### Step [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m: Update Test to Enable Flag[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mIn `RTFParserTest.java` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m517[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m528[0m[39m, `[0m[1;35mtestJavaObj[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Configure the parser to allow Java serialized objects for this specific test:[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```java[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  @Test[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  public void [0m[1;35mtestJavaObj[0m[1;39m([0m[39m@TempDir Path tmpDir[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m throws Exception [0m[1;39m{[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Create parser with flag enabled[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      RTFParser parser = new [0m[1;35mRTFParser[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;35mparser.setAllowJavaSerializedObjects[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtrue[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Existing test logic[0m[33m...[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Justification[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Optimal Security Posture**: Disabling by default prevents exploitation on all [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msystems by default, requiring explicit opt-in[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Preserves Existing Logic**: [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Safe OBJDATA and PICT handling paths are completely unchanged[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Only affects the dangerous JAVA_OBJDATA path[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Exception handling in TextExtractor already catches TikaException [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m1476[0m[1;39m)[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Addresses Evaluation Report**:[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Eliminates the [0m[32m"Unrestricted class/object creation based on externally [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32mcontrolled data"[0m[39m vulnerability[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Provides clear error message when disabled[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Allows tracking and auditing when enabled through configuration[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Backward Compatibility**:[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Existing deployments become secure by default without changes[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Users who truly need this feature can explicitly enable it via Tika XML [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconfiguration[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Follows established configuration pattern in the codebase[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **No Side Effects**:[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Does not modify utility functions, fuzzing logic, or test frameworks[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Does not break other embedded object types [0m[1;39m([0m[39mOLE, pictures, etc.[0m[1;39m)[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Only affects the narrow JAVA_OBJDATA deserialization path[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Test updates are minimal and necessary only for the specific Java object test[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. **Similar Solutions**: The `ignoreListMarkup` flag [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m57[0m[39m in RTFParser.java[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdemonstrates the exact same pattern for security-related configuration[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Potential Side Effects and Mitigations[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Breaking Change for Java Object Feature Users**: [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Mitigation: Clear error message explaining how to re-enable[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Impact: Minimal - this is an obscure RTF feature rarely used in practice[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Test Failure**: [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Mitigation: Update `[0m[1;35mtestJavaObj[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to explicitly enable the flag[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This demonstrates how users can opt-in if needed[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Configuration Complexity**:[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Mitigation: Document the flag in parser configuration examples[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Users can enable via standard Tika XML config[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Security Considerations[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis approach provides defense-in-depth:[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Default deny**: Feature disabled unless explicitly enabled[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Fail-safe**: Throws exception rather than silently skipping[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Auditable**: Configuration makes it clear when dangerous feature is enabled[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Minimal attack surface**: Only affects one specific control word handler[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fix eliminates the RCE vulnerability reported by Jazzer while maintaining the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mability to opt-in for legitimate use cases if they exist.[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue reports a **Remote Code Execution [0m[1;39m([0m[39mRCE[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m** vulnerability in Apache[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTika's RTF parser module. The vulnerability arises from unrestricted Java object [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeserialization when processing RTF files containing embedded Java serialized [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mobjects. A fuzzer [0m[1;39m([0m[39mJazzer[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m detected this security issue at [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mRTFEmbObjHandler.handleCompletedObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` line [0m[1;36m217[0m[39m, where [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mObjectInputStream.readObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` is called without validation.[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patch attempt introduces a security control by adding a configuration flag [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`allowJavaSerializedObjects` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdefaulting to `false`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to disable Java object [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeserialization. However, the patch fails to compile because it references [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`TikaSecurityException`, a class that does not exist in the [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39morg.apache.tika.exception package.[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Initial Issue Analysis[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe vulnerability stack trace reveals:[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Entry Point**: The fuzzer invokes `[0m[1;35mRTFParser.parse[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` through [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mRTFParserFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Vulnerable Code Path**: [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `[0m[1;35mRTFParser.parseInline[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` → `[0m[1;35mTextExtractor.extract[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` → [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mTextExtractor.processGroupEnd[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` → `[0m[1;35mRTFEmbObjHandler.handleCompletedObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Critical Line**: At `RTFEmbObjHandler.jav[0m[1;92ma:217[0m[39m`, the code calls [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mObjectInputStream.readObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to deserialize Java objects embedded in RTF files[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Security Issue**: The deserialization occurs without any validation or [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallowlist of permitted classes, enabling arbitrary code execution if malicious [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mserialized objects are embedded in RTF files[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe Jazzer security hook [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;35mjaz.Zer.readObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m correctly identifies this as a [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhigh-severity security issue, classifying it as [0m[32m"Unrestricted class/object creation[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32mbased on externally controlled data."[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Patch Attempt Details[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patch modifies three files:[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**[0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. RTFParser.java modifications:**[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Adds a new boolean field `allowJavaSerializedObjects` with default value `false`[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Adds getter `[0m[1;35misAllowJavaSerializedObjects[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and setter [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35msetAllowJavaSerializedObjects[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` methods[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Modifies the `[0m[1;35mparseInline[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method to pass this flag to `RTFEmbObjHandler` [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconstructor[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**[0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. RTFEmbObjHandler.java modifications:**[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Adds import statement: `import org.apache.tika.exception.TikaSecurityException;`[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Adds a new final boolean field `allowJavaSerializedObjects` to the class[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Updates constructor signature to accept the new parameter[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Adds a security check in `[0m[1;35mhandleCompletedObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method before Java [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeserialization [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m217[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Throws `TikaSecurityException` if `allowJavaSerializedObjects` is false[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Provides descriptive error message about the security restriction[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**[0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. RTFParserTest.java modifications:**[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Updates the `[0m[1;35mtestJavaObj[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` test method to:[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Create an RTFParser instance[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Enable Java serialized objects via `[0m[1;35msetAllowJavaSerializedObjects[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtrue[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Add the parser to ParseContext[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Pass the parser to `[0m[1;35mgetRecursiveMetadata[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Compilation Failure[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patch fails with two compilation errors in `RTFEmbObjHandler.java`:[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Line [0m[1;36m34[0m[39m**: `cannot find symbol: class TikaSecurityException` in the import [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstatement[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Line [0m[1;36m218[0m[39m**: `cannot find symbol: class TikaSecurityException` at the throw [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstatement[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe root cause is that `TikaSecurityException` does not exist in the [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`org.apache.tika.exception` package in the current codebase. The patch assumes this[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexception class is available but it is not defined.[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTo properly address this vulnerability and fix the compilation issue, the following[0m [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpackage to determine:[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - What security-related exception classes currently exist[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Whether to use an existing exception [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., `TikaException`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m or create a new [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`TikaSecurityException` class[0m                                                       [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mhandleCompletedObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method to understand:[0m                                     [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtika-parsers/tika-parsers-standard/tika-parsers-standard-modules/tika-parser-micros[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moft-module/src/test/java/org/apache/tika/parser/microsoft/rtf/RTFParserTest.jav[0m[1;92ma:51[0m [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m517[0m[39m:    public void [0m[1;35mtestJavaObj[0m[1;39m([0m[39m@TempDir Path tmpDir[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m throws Exception [0m[1;39m{[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m518[0m[39m:        String rtf = [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mIOUtils.resourceToString[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"/test-documents/rtf/rtfJavaObjTemplate.rtf"[0m[39m,[0m              [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m524[0m[39m:        List<Metadata> metadata = [0m[1;35mgetRecursiveMetadata[0m[1;39m([0m[39mp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m525[0m[39m:        [0m[1;35massertEquals[0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m2[0m[39m, [0m[1;35mmetadata.size[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m526[0m[39m:        [0m[1;35massertEquals[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"java.lang.String"[0m[39m, [0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mmetadata.get[0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.get[0m[1;39m([0m[39mRTFMetadata.EMB_CLASS[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m527[0m[39m:        [0m[1;35massertContains[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"the quick brown fox"[0m[39m, [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mmetadata.get[0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.get[0m[1;39m([0m[39mTikaCoreProperties.TIKA_CONTENT[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m528[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Analysis[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Core Issues Identified[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Compilation Error**: The patch references `TikaSecurityException` which [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdoesn't exist in the codebase[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Security Vulnerability**: Unrestricted Java deserialization in [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mRTFEmbObjHandler.handleCompletedObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` at line [0m[1;36m217[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Test Configuration**: The test needs to be updated to enable the security flag[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfor Java deserialization[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Root Cause Analysis[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe last patch attempt correctly identified the vulnerability and the mitigation [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstrategy [0m[1;39m([0m[39madd a configuration flag to control Java deserialization[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, but failed [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbecause:[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- It attempted to import and throw `TikaSecurityException` which is not defined in [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe codebase[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The existing exception hierarchy in `org.apache.tika.exception` includes [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`TikaException`, `AccessPermissionException`, and `TikaMemoryLimitException`, but [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mno `TikaSecurityException`[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Code Inspection Insights[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mFrom the relevant code snippets:[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. The base exception class `TikaException` exists with simple constructors [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39maccepting message and optional cause[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Security-related exceptions like `AccessPermissionException` extend [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`TikaException` [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. The `@Field` annotation pattern is established for parser configuration [0m[1;39m([0m[39msee [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`memoryLimitInKb`, `ignoreListMarkup`[0m[1;39m)[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Configuration flows: RTFParser → [0m[1;35mparseInline[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m → RTFEmbObjHandler constructor → [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mhandleCompletedObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Test infrastructure supports passing configured parser instances via [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mgetRecursiveMetadata[0m[1;39m([0m[39mPath, Parser, boolean[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Approach: Use TikaException Directly [0m[1;39m([0m[39mNo New Exception Class[0m[1;39m)[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mRather than creating a new `TikaSecurityException` class [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwhich would require [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmodifying tika-core[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, we'll use `TikaException` directly with a clear [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msecurity-focused error message. This approach:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Avoids compilation errors[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Follows existing patterns [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., `TikaMemoryLimitException` also extends [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`TikaException`[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Clearly communicates the security issue through the message[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Is simpler and safer for a security patch[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Implementation Steps[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m#### [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. Modify RTFParser.java[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAdd the security configuration field following the established pattern:[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Location**: After line [0m[1;36m57[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mafter `ignoreListMarkup` field[0m[1;39m)[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Add field: `@Field private boolean allowJavaSerializedObjects = false;`[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Default to `false` for security [0m[1;39m([0m[39mopt-in for dangerous deserialization[0m[1;39m)[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Location**: After line [0m[1;36m115[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mafter `[0m[1;35msetMemoryLimitInKb[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method[0m[1;39m)[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Add getter: `public boolean [0m[1;35misAllowJavaSerializedObjects[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m return [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallowJavaSerializedObjects; [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m`[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Add setter with `@Field` annotation: `public void [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35msetAllowJavaSerializedObjects[0m[1;39m([0m[39mboolean allowJavaSerializedObjects[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthis.allowJavaSerializedObjects = allowJavaSerializedObjects; [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m`[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Location**: Line [0m[1;36m93[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mmodify RTFEmbObjHandler constructor call[0m[1;39m)[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Change: `new [0m[1;35mRTFEmbObjHandler[0m[1;39m([0m[39mhandler, metadata, context, [0m[1;35mgetMemoryLimitInKb[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- To: `new [0m[1;35mRTFEmbObjHandler[0m[1;39m([0m[39mhandler, metadata, context, [0m[1;35mgetMemoryLimitInKb[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m#### [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. Modify RTFParserTest.java[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Location**: Line [0m[1;36m517[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m524[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mtestJavaObj method[0m[1;39m)[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Replace line [0m[1;36m524[0m[39m: `List<Metadata> metadata = [0m[1;35mgetRecursiveMetadata[0m[1;39m([0m[39mp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`[0m            [2m                [0m
