[2;36m                    [0m         [39mList<Metadata> metadata = [0m[1;35mgetRecursiveMetadata[0m[1;39m([0m[39mp, parser, false[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis creates a configured parser instance, enables Java deserialization, and passes[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mit to the test method.[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Justification[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m#### Why This Approach is Optimal[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Fixes Compilation Error**: By using `TikaException` instead of the [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnon-existent `TikaSecurityException`, the code will compile successfully[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Addresses Security Vulnerability**: [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Default-deny approach [0m[1;39m([0m[39mflag defaults to `false`[0m[1;39m)[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Blocks dangerous deserialization unless explicitly enabled[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Clear error message warns about RCE risk[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Security check happens before any deserialization attempt[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Preserves Existing Logic**:[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - When flag is `true`, original functionality is preserved[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No changes to other EMB_STATE cases [0m[1;39m([0m[39mOBJDATA, PICT, NADA[0m[1;39m)[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Existing tests continue to work [0m[1;39m([0m[39mexcept testJavaObj which needs configuration[0m[1;39m)[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No impact on non-Java embedded objects[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Follows Established Patterns**:[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Uses `@Field` annotation like `ignoreListMarkup` and `memoryLimitInKb`[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Constructor parameter passing pattern matches `memoryLimitInKb`[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Test configuration follows patterns from other parser tests[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Exception handling consistent with other security checks[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Minimal Surface Area**:[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Only modifies files directly related to the vulnerability[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No changes to tika-core module[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No new classes or complex refactoring[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Surgical fix focused on the exact vulnerability location[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m#### How It Addresses the Evaluation Report[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Initial Issue**: RCE via unrestricted [0m[1;35mObjectInputStream.readObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m → FIXED by[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39madding security check[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Compilation Error**: TikaSecurityException doesn't exist → FIXED by using [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTikaException[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Test Failure**: testJavaObj needs configuration → FIXED by passing configured [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparser[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m#### Potential Side Effects and Mitigation[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Breaking Change for Existing Users**: [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Users processing RTF files with embedded Java objects will get exceptions by [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdefault[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Mitigation**: This is intentional security hardening; users must explicitly [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mopt-in via configuration[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Clear error message guides users on how to enable if needed[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Test Suite Impact**:[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Only testJavaObj is affected [0m[1;39m([0m[39mtests embedded Java objects[0m[1;39m)[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Mitigation**: Test is updated to explicitly enable the flag[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Other tests unaffected as they don't use Java object deserialization[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Backwards Compatibility**:[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Default behavior becomes more restrictive [0m[1;39m([0m[39mblocks Java deserialization[0m[1;39m)[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Mitigation**: This is appropriate for a security vulnerability; users can [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrestore old behavior via configuration[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Non-Java embedded objects [0m[1;39m([0m[39mOBJDATA, PICT[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m continue to work normally[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m#### Similar Solutions in Codebase[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis approach mirrors existing security controls:[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `AccessChecker` in PDFParser [0m[1;39m([0m[39mchecks permissions before extraction[0m[1;39m)[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `memoryLimitInKb` in RTFParser [0m[1;39m([0m[39msafety limit on memory allocation[0m[1;39m)[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Both use configuration flags with safe defaults and clear exceptions[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Error Message Rationale[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe error message explicitly:[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. States the restriction: [0m[32m"Java object deserialization is disabled"[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Explains the reason: [0m[32m"for security reasons"[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Warns about the risk: [0m[32m"Deserializing untrusted data may enable remote code [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32mexecution"[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Provides remediation: [0m[32m"Set [0m[32mallowJavaSerializedObjects[0m[32m=[0m[32mtrue[0m[32m in RTFParser [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32mconfiguration"[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis empowers users to make informed decisions about security vs. functionality [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtradeoffs.[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m
